Wiring notes:
  - opencode-plugin's per-tool execute() now calls executeWithApproval(def, toolCallId,
    parsed, rt.ctx, { sqlTx: rt.quotaSql, sqlListen: rt.listenSql, sqlRules: rt.quotaSql }).
  - rt.listenSql = postgres(databaseUrl.replace(':6543', ':5432'), {max:1, idle_timeout:0,
    application_name:'basics-worker-approvals-listen'}).
  - teardownRuntime() closes listenSql + quotaSql with 2s timeout.
  - Fast paths (no .approval, decision.required=false, approval_rule matched)
    skip the LISTEN entirely and run def.execute directly.
